  "text": "Kubernetes RBAC authorization is implemented across multiple packages that work together to enforce role-based access control:\n\n## Core Authorization Logic\n\n**RBACAuthorizer** (`plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go`): The main authorizer implementing the `authorizer.Authorizer` interface. The `Authorize()` method uses a `RequestToRuleMapper` to evaluate whether a request should be allowed by checking if any policy rules apply to the user.\n\n**DefaultRuleResolver** (`pkg/registry/rbac/validation/rule.go`): Implements the rule resolution logic by querying Role, RoleBinding, ClusterRole, and ClusterRoleBinding resources. Methods include:\n- `RulesFor()`: Returns all applicable rules for a user\n- `VisitRulesFor()`: Iterates through rules with a visitor pattern\n- `GetRoleReferenceRules()`: Resolves a role reference to its policy rules\n\n**SubjectAccessEvaluator** (`plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/subject_locator.go`): Determines which subjects (users, groups, service accounts) can perform a given action. Implements the `SubjectLocator` interface with the `AllowedSubjects()` method.\n\n## REST API Handlers\n\nSubjectAccessReview resources enable clients to check access permissions:\n- **SubjectAccessReview** (`pkg/registry/authorization/subjectaccessreview/rest.go`): Cluster-scoped access review\n- **LocalSubjectAccessReview** (`pkg/registry/authorization/localsubjectaccessreview/rest.go`): Namespace-scoped access review\n- **SelfSubjectAccessReview** (`pkg/registry/authorization/selfsubjectaccessreview/rest.go`): Check current user's access\n- **SelfSubjectRulesReview** (`pkg/registry/authorization/selfsubjectrulesreview/rest.go`): List rules available to current user\n- **RESTStorageProvider** (`pkg/registry/authorization/rest/storage_authorization.go`): Registers these handlers\n\n## Bootstrap RBAC Policies\n\nInitial RBAC policy definitions are provided by:\n- `policy.go`: Defines system ClusterRoles and ClusterRoleBindings (including system:admin, system:nodes, etc.)\n- `namespace_policy.go`: Provides namespace-scoped Roles and RoleBindings (e.g., edit, view roles)\n- `controller_policy.go`: Defines roles for system controllers\n\nThese are reconciled during API server startup via the PostStartHook mechanism in `pkg/registry/rbac/rest/storage_rbac.go`.\n\n## Policy-Based Storage with Escalation Prevention\n\nRole and Binding resources use policy-based storage implementations that prevent privilege escalation:\n\n- **Role** (`pkg/registry/rbac/role/policybased/storage.go`): Wraps standard storage to validate that users cannot grant themselves permissions they don't already have\n- **ClusterRole** (`pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrole/policybased/storage.go`): Validates escalation, including aggregation rules\n- **RoleBinding** (`pkg/registry/rbac/rolebinding/policybased/storage.go`): Checks binding authorization\n- **ClusterRoleBinding** (`pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrolebinding/policybased/storage.go`): Checks binding authorization at cluster scope\n\nAll storage implementations use:\n- `EscalationAllowed()` (`pkg/registry/rbac/escalation_check.go`): Checks if user is system:masters\n- `RoleEscalationAuthorized()`: Checks explicit escalate permission\n- `BindingAuthorized()`: Checks bind permission for role references\n- `ConfirmNoEscalation()` and `ConfirmNoEscalationInternal()` (`pkg/registry/rbac/validation/rule.go`): Validates user rules cover requested rules\n\nThese mechanisms ensure that users can only create or modify roles/bindings if they already possess all permissions being granted."
}

